this is a template for "OmniCode Documentation":
    keyed as "B-word-omni-seed-documentation"
    following "CWS-STD-006 (5-Block Documentation)"

this template classifies as:
    independent (1) when "standalone reference documentation"
    connected (0) when "part of documentation set" such as "[related docs]"
    dependent (-1) when "requiring external standards" such as "[list them]"

this template derives from:
    original (1) when "establishing new documentation pattern in OmniCode"
    derived (0) from "B-word-omni-seed-universal"
    variant (-1) when "intentionally departing from standard"
    documented at "bereshit/word/omni/seed/"

this template strictness is:
    tight (1) meaning "Follow exactly - 5-block structure, required sections"
    guided (0) meaning "Adapt thoughtfully - content within structure"
    free (-1) meaning "Principles only - teaching comments, examples"

to use this template:
    copy and adapt for new OmniCode documentation files
    replace [bracketed] placeholders with actual content
    change pragma from "template" to "documentation" when complete
    remove this preamble section when adapted

// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

core identity of this document:

    grounded in:
        scripture "[Relevant verse grounding this document's purpose]"
            from [Book Chapter:Verse] in [KJV/WEB]
        principle "[Kingdom principle this document demonstrates]"
        anchor "[Supporting verse reinforcing the principle]"
            from [Book Chapter:Verse] in [KJV/WEB]

    serves as [Reference/Guide/Standard/Tutorial]:
        role "[Specific responsibility in documentation architecture]"
        paradigm "5-Block Documentation"

    authored by:
        architect "[Who designed the document structure and scope]"
        writer "[Who wrote and refined the content]"
        created [YYYY-MM-DD]
        version [MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH]
        modified [YYYY-MM-DD] for "[what changed]"

    exists to:
        purpose "[What question does this document answer?]"
        design "[Document type and organizational pattern]"
        philosophy "[Guiding principle for how this document serves readers]"
        features:
            "[Major teaching 1 - what readers learn]"
            "[Major teaching 2 - what readers can do after]"
            "[Major teaching 3 - what problems it solves]"

interface of this document:

    depends on:
        requires (1) "[prerequisite knowledge or document]" for "[foundational understanding]"
        includes (0) "[related document]" for "[optional deeper context]"
        excludes (-1) "[out-of-scope topic]" because "[covered elsewhere or intentionally omitted]"
        used by "[Who reads this document - roles, use cases]"
        integrates with "[Related documentation and standards]"

    integrated as:
        reading "[scan/skim/read/study/reference]" for "[layered comprehension]"
        navigation "[section anchors and cross-references]" for "[quick access]"
        complete (1) for "reader understands and can apply"
        partial (0) for "reader needs additional context"
        confused (-1) for "reader needs prerequisite reading"

operational context of this document:

    blocking:
        [yes (1) / conditional (0) / no (-1)] because "[is this prerequisite for other docs?]"
        mitigation "[what to read if this doc is unavailable]"

    health:
        system Base100 with scale from -100 to +100
        granted (1) above +50 meaning "document serves readers well"
        deferred (0) within ±50 meaning "document needs refinement"
        denied (-1) below -50 meaning "document requires major revision"

        operations:
            "[clarity of explanation]" scores +[X] (1) for "[concepts well explained]"
            "[example coverage]" scores 0 (0) for "[examples adequate]"
            "[missing sections]" scores -[X] (-1) for "[gaps in coverage]"

        cascade multipliers:
            "[prerequisite document health]" multiplies by [X] because "[foundations affect understanding]"

